snippet.textDisplay:
Might as well leave a cold-ass lil comment here before dis vizzle officially becomes a whole week old.

When tha Kalos League final match aired, I clowninly axed "how will Alain take tha win?" but held up a inch of hope dat Ash would come up wit suttin' ta conquer one of his wild lil' freakadelic top billin opponents up in Kalos, as he lost ta his ass twice before. Needless ta say, he lost tha League, again, n' he lost ta Alain, fo' tha third time up in a row. If his thugged-out lil' punk-ass beat Ash three times up in succession, I guess da thug wasn't like tha worthy opponent dat Alain was searchin fo' afta all, huh, biatch? Tough break fo' both of dem wild-ass muthafuckas.

And tha way tha match concluded did seem a lil' bit forced. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Charizard took da most thugged-out damage it probably eva took up in Alainz entire League run, n' yet dat shiznit was barely scratched up in tha end, just so Ash could fall as hard as possible. What a thugged-out dballa n' shiznit fo' realz. All dat hard work, all dat shovin it down our throats dat Ash wanted ta win dis league, n' dis is what tha fuck it amounted to.

It aint nuthin but pretty likely dat all tha dialogue hintin at Ashz potential success up in tha Kalos League was all just tha creators screwin wit tha viewers' mindz up in a thugged-out desperate attempt ta win back tha crew they lost wit tha maligned Unova saga yo, but I too wish ta believe that, wit all tha hints they presented all up in tha series n' tha incredible amount of pimpment Ash was given as tha XY n' XY&Z seasons progressed, not ta mention tha decision ta give his ass a juice boost fo' one of his Pokemon dat only he ridin' solo could use, they initially had every last muthafuckin intention of lettin tha kid win tha League fo' once up in his wild lil' fuckin eternally 10-year oldschool game yo, but tha executives all up in tha basement behind dis show disapproved of dat decision n' chizzled it straight-up late up in tha game ta give our asses what tha fuck was ultimately shown on televizzle.

I be thinkin why they still wouldn't allow Ash ta win a single League ta dis straight-up dizzle is outta these naggin fears:

1. That tha show would gotta chizzle its formula ta suttin' they likely believe would be too different ta be called tha same show no mo', afta 19 muthafuckin yearz of pretty much tha same thang over n' over again.
2. That Ashz pimpment would have reached its apex n' they would have not a god damn thang left ta do wit his ass afta havin his ass as tha main protagonist since tha inception of tha show, even though as a eternal 10-year old, there will always be much fo' his ass ta learn, no matta how tha fuck phat of a trainer he is.
3. That tha lil pimps watchin would take a positizzle pay-off ta all of Ashz mad bullshit n' glorious victories straight-up seriously ta tha point dat they'll peep his ass as perfect, n' be thinkin dat if they strain theyselves as da ruffneck did, they'd also be perfect, n' would grow up tha fuck into egotistical a-holez whoz ass could never take a loss, even if some sense was talked tha fuck into dem by they elders.

This is just me speculatin yo, but I can't help feelin there be a at least SOME kind of reason thatz holdin dis show back from goin dat one extra mile n' bein tha pimped out piece of animated entertainment dat it could be, especially fo' tha fact itz based on a hot-pimpin franchise dat playas all round tha ghetto ludd n' can't git enough of.

Yes, all up in tha end of tha day, itz aimed at lil pimps yo, but when you draw lil pimps tha fuck into dis show, hold they interest wit yo' storytellin n' make dem root fo' tha characters, whoz ass grow ta become they favorites, don't they deserve ta be rewarded properly fo' they investment n' positizzle feedback, biatch? Yes, dis show existed, n' always will exist, ta push tha vizzle game n' other formz of merchandise. But dat fact shouldn't prevent tha writas from puttin some effort tha fuck into makin tha highest qualitizzle thang they can. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. If they did, tha higher-ups cook up a profit off tha loot sales, tha viewers git they entertainin content, dem hoes wins.
